article.headline: Bradley 79, Evansville 76 (OT)
article.story: EVANSVILLE, Ind. (AP) -- Marcellus Sommerville scored 28 points, including the game-clinching free throws, as Bradley beat Evansville 79-76 in overtime Saturday night in the Missouri Valley Conference. Sommerville scored nine points in overtime, nearly doubling his first-half production of five. Jason Holsinger, who finished with 19 for Evansville (5-14, 1-10 MVC), tied the game at 66 by sinking a 3-pointer with 38 seconds left in regulation, then Bradley Strickland blocked a last-ditch shot by the Braves with three seconds left to force overtime. Bradley (12-7, 6-5) outscored the Purple Aces 13-10 in the extra period as five of Sommerville's nine points came at the line. Patrick O'Bryant scored 16 and Lawrence Wright 11 for the Braves. Daniel Ruffin contributed eight assists. Kyle Anslinger led Evansville with 20, and Matt Webster had 17. Evansville led 37-30 at halftime but was outscored 36-29 after the break.
